<main id="main">
    <h1>New: Working with reorders</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">New beta version of the reorder</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This manual page describes how to reorder goods and manage reorders using the beta version of the new reorder functionality. As soon as the test phase ends, the functionality will be implemented in all plentymarkets systems during the upcoming weeks. Until then, you can find further information on the upcoming release in this <a href="https://forum.plentymarkets.com/t/ankuendigung-releaseprozess-neue-nachbestellung/542252" target="_blank" rel="noopener">forum post</a> (Last update: 24-May-2019).</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Stock » Reorder management » Purchase order</strong> menu, you do not only carry out <a href="/en/stock-management/working-with-redistributions">redistributions</a>, but you also create reorders. Reorders are used to reorder goods from your suppliers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A reorder consists of the following steps:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Identifying variations for the reorder:</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#300">Creating a reorder</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#400">Adding order items</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#500">Editing order items</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#600">Submitting additional information</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#700">Finishing and sending a reorder</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#800">Using the backlog list</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#900">Booking items in</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="#1000">Finishing a reorder</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>We recommend carrying out some preparatory settings before working with reorders.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Preparatory settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following chapters describe some preparatory settings. Carry them out before working with reorders for the first time. Usually, these settings only have to be made once. Set up the reorder level and the quantity suggestion for reorders to determine when items should be reordered. Create new order statuses especially for reorders and create tags to maintain a good overview. In addition, setting up a document for the <strong>reorder</strong> document is mandatory.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="110">1.1. Setting up the reorder level and quantity suggestion</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Prior to creating your first reorder, you should carry out the settings for the reorder level and the sales period. This way, you determine at which stock level variations are reordered.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the reorder level and quantity suggestion:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » System settings » Stock » Reorder management » Reorder » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to the information provided in &lt;table-reorder-level-quantity-suggestion-reorder&gt;.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
